abstract: “It’s hard to look at Washington or look at Iowa and think that our national politics is working.”

abstract: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
snippet: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Democratic officials in Iowa on Tuesday provided a measure of clarity to the muddled outcome of its statewide caucuses, releasing a delayed first wave of partial results that showed Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders with a preliminary lead and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. falling well behind the other top-tier candidates.

abstract: How a political ritual turned into a political nightmare.
snippet: How a political ritual turned into a political nightmare.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Every four years the Iowa caucuses are supposed to deliver the first clear signal of which candidates are actually resonating with voters. That didn’t happen on Monday.

headline_main: Breakdown in Iowa: Oh What a Night!
headline_print_headline: Breakdown in Iowa: Oh What a Night!

abstract: Only a handful of states and territories will try to pick the Democratic nominee with similar practices as Iowa, where officials faced delays and problems reporting results.
snippet: Only a handful of states and territories will try to pick the Democratic nominee with similar practices as Iowa, where officials faced delays and problems reporting results.
lead_paragraph: As Iowa grapples with the aftermath of a Democratic caucus that one party leader called a “systemwide disaster,” American voters and election officials are already looking ahead at the handful of other states and American territories that will be picking — or trying to pick — the Democratic nominee in similar ways.

abstract: We’re moving on to New Hampshire, but we’re still stuck in Iowa. This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: We’re moving on to New Hampshire, but we’re still stuck in Iowa. This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: No winner emerged from the Iowa caucuses last night. But, in the wee hours of the morning, at least one thing became official: In 2020, we cannot have nice things.
